<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,353,704]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,353,380]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Surstylus with approximately 8 apically blunt, peg-like teeth (ch.37-0); both anterior postgonites basally with strongly sclerotized, large flaps asymmetric in shape.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1437,353,704]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,528,425,452]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Supplementary description</emphasis>
(not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[978,1100,426,452]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosa">
<emphasis box="[978,995,426,451]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1014,1100,426,451]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">spinosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Supracervical setae 27–29. Arista with arb = 2/0. Cibarial, medial sensilla approximately 9 per side; posterior sensilla approximately 6 per side. Abdominal sternite III wider than long (ch.22-1). Pregonite with sensilla on submedial portion (ch.52-1). Posterior postgonite only on right side of aedeagal sheath; left, anterior postgonite apically strongly sclerotized and bifurcated, but right one not.
</paragraph>
